My crazy simple coil jig for putting washers on coil cores. Cheap, simple and it works. Best with my cores and washers to match the knurling. Use a mallet on a flat spot, move over to "top" or "bottom" hammer on, then straighten the washers as necessary. Usually they come out flat if you hammer them really straight. I use a hand drill with a rod and threaded end and eyeball them as it turns and tweak as needed for super flat coil washers. I have about 20 jigs left on the website, tons of coil washers, tons of coil cores in different styles. www.infiniteirons.com
